
❯ how Create a service account

⏺ Step 1 — Link Play Console to Google Cloud

  1. Open https://play.google.com/console
  2. Go to Setup → API access
  3. Click Link to a Google Cloud project → choose an existing project or create a new one
  4. Click Learn how to create service accounts (opens Google Cloud Console)

  ---
  Step 2 — Create the Service Account in Google Cloud

  1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts
  2. Select your linked project
  3. Click + Create Service Account
  4. Fill in:
    - Name: hislo-play-deploy (or any name)
    - ID: auto-filled
  5. Click Create and Continue → skip the optional roles → click Done

  ---
  Step 3 — Generate the JSON Key

  1. Click on the service account you just created
  2. Go to Keys tab → Add Key → Create new key
  3. Choose JSON → click Create
  4. A .json file downloads automatically
  5. Move it to ~/.credentials/:
  mkdir -p ~/.credentials
  mv ~/Downloads/*.json ~/.credentials/hislo-play-service-account.json

  ---
  Step 4 — Grant Access in Play Console

  1. Go back to Play Console → Setup → API access
  2. Find the service account in the list → click Grant access
  3. Set role to Release Manager
  4. Click Apply → Save

  ---
  Step 5 — Fill in .playstore.env

  PLAY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=/Users/shgardii/.credentials/hislo-play-service-account.json
  PLAY_PACKAGE_NAME=sa.revival.hislo
  PLAY_TRACK=internal
